I'm not normally a "salad-person".  Somehow, Lisa makes salads taste SO good that I find myself craving her leafy-greens on a regular basis.  The cranberry salad is my favorite.  The steak in the steak salad was a little too well-done.  I wish that my server had given me the option med-rare on that one.  The balls are yummy - I just wish that they came with a side salad (here I go with the leafy greens again...).  The green tea is my favorite drink there - very refreshing.    I wish that the lunch prices were $2 lower and that the acoustics were a little better in there.  Maybe lay down a few rugs?  The bathrooms are nice though!

